2025-09-10 17:26:04 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:04 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-10 17:26:04 [INFO] Can continue: What's wrong?
2025-09-10 17:26:04 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:05 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:05 [INFO] Can continue: You may or may not be aware, but a plague has<br>spread across West Ardougne. Now, so far, our efforts<br>to contain it have been largely successful, for the most<br>part.
2025-09-10 17:26:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Can continue: However, some sheep recently escaped from a farm<br>near the city. When they were found, we noticed that<br>they were strangely discoloured, so we asked the<br>mourners to examine them.
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Can continue: They believe that the sheep have become infected with<br>the plague.
2025-09-10 17:26:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:08 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:08 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:08 [INFO] Can continue: As the councillor responsible for public health and safety<br>here in East Ardougne, I am in charge of dealing with<br>this problem.
2025-09-10 17:26:08 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:09 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:09 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:09 [INFO] Can continue: We need someone to herd these sheep into a safe<br>enclosure, kill them quickly and cleanly and then dispose<br>of the remains hygienically in a special incinerator.
2025-09-10 17:26:09 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Can continue: Unfortunately, nobody wants to risk catching the plague,<br>and I am unable to find someone willing to undertake<br>this mission for me.
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] ===
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] Yes.
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] No.
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] ===
2025-09-10 17:26:10 [INFO] 1353 Option: 1 Yes.
2025-09-10 17:26:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:12 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-10 17:26:12 [INFO] Can continue: I can do that for you.
2025-09-10 17:26:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:13 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:13 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:13 [INFO] Can continue: You will? That is excellent news! Head to the enclosure<br>we have set up on Farmer Brumty's land to the north<br>of the city; the four infected sheep should still be<br>somewhere in that vicinity.
2025-09-10 17:26:13 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Can continue: Before you will be allowed to enter the enclosure,<br>however, you must ensure you have some kind of<br>protective clothing to prevent contagion.
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Can continue: Where can I find some protective clothing then?
2025-09-10 17:26:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Can continue: Doctor Orbon should have something suitable. You<br>should be able to find him in the chapel just north of<br>here.
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Can continue: Councillor Halgrive
2025-09-10 17:26:15 [INFO] Can continue: Please also take this poisoned sheep feed; we believe<br>poisoning the sheep will minimise the risk of airborne<br>contamination, and is of course also more humane to<br>the sheep.
